    "# Key Insights\n",
    "\n",
    "- The AI Premium: AI-related roles offer a significantly higher median salary and clear premium across almost all U.S. states compared to non-AI positions.\n",
    "- Work Arrangement Flexibility: Fully remote and hybrid roles match or outpace traditional on-site (\"Not Remote\") distribution curves, signaling no financial penalty for flexible environments.\n",
    "- Industry Wage Volatility: Tech-adjacent sectors, particularly Agents for Wireless Telecommunications, exhibit massive monthly wage growth and volatility, while traditional industries like manufacturing remain flat.\n",
    "\n",
    "# Recommendations for Job Seekers\n",
    "\n",
    "- Target AI Upskilling: Integrate AI skills such as programming, machine learning, agentic AI capabilities into your current skill set to unlock higher baseline salaries.\n",
    "- Geographic Arbitrage: Utilize fully remote roles to secure high-paying positions anchored in tech-heavy regions without needing to relocate.\n",
    "- Timing over Tech-Adjacent Roles: If target industries involve high-volatility salary trends (like telecommunications), expect highly fluid compensation structures and time your negotiations during peak market upswings."
